properties.name: Angkor Wat, Angkor, Cambodia.
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraAngkor Wat (or Angkor Vat) is a temple at Angkor, Cambodia, built for King Suryavarman II in the early 12th century as his state temple and capital city.

properties.name: Arizona Meteor Crater, Arizona, USA
properties.description: Posted by Simulacra

properties.name: Cerne Abbas Giant, Cerne Abbas, Dorset, England.
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraThe Cerne Abbas giant is a hill figure of a giant naked man on a hillside near the village of Cerne Abbas to the north of Dorchester in Dorset, England.

properties.name: Easter Island
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraEaster Island (Rapa Nui in Tahitian and today also in Rapa Nui language, Isla de Pascua in Spanish) is an island in the south Pacific Ocean belonging to Chile. The island is famous for its numerous moai, the stone statues located along the coastlines.

properties.name: Face
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraA formation of rocks that resembles a face. 50° 0\'38.20"N 110° 6\'48.32"W

properties.name: Glastonbury Tor, Glastonbury, Somerset, England
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraGlastonbury Tor is a teardrop-shaped hill at Glastonbury, Somerset, England, with its only standing architectural feature the roofless St Michael\'s Tower of the former church.

properties.name: Groom Lake, Area 51, Nevada
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraArea 51 (also known as Air Force Flight Test Center (Detachment 3)[1], Dreamland, Paradise Ranch[2], Home Base, Watertown Strip, Groom Lake[3], The Box, Neverland, and other names) is a remote tract of land in the southwestern portion of Lincoln County in southern Nevada.

properties.name: Machu Picchu, Peru
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraMachu Pikchu Old Peak; sometimes called the "Lost City".

properties.description: Posted by Simulacra

properties.name: Mont Saint-Michel, Normandy
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraMont Saint-Michel (English: Mount Saint Michael) is a rocky tidal island in Normandy, roughly one kilometre from the north coast of France at the mouth of the Couesnon River near Avranches.

properties.name: Pyramid of the Sun, Teotihuacán, Mexico
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraThe Pyramid of the Sun is the largest building in Teotihuacán and one of the largest in Mesoamerica. Found along the Avenue of the Dead, in between the Pyramid of the Moon and the Ciudadela, and in the shadow of the massive mountain Cerro Gordo, the pyramid is part of a large complex in the heart of the city.

properties.name: Pyramids of Giza, Cairo, Egypt
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraPyramids of GizaThe Giza Necropolis stands on the Giza Plateau, on the outskirts of Cairo, Egypt.

properties.name: Stonehenge, Wiltshire, England
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraStonehenge is a prehistoric monument located in the English county of Wiltshire, about 8 miles (13 km) north of Salisbury

properties.name: The Pentagon, Arlington, Virginia, USA
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraThe Pentagon is the headquarters of the United States Department of Defense, located in Arlington, Virginia. As a symbol of the U.S. military, "the Pentagon" is often used metonymically to refer to the Department of Defense rather than the building itself.

properties.name: Troy, Turkey
properties.description: Posted by SimulacraTroy (Greek: Τροία, Troia, also Ίλιον, Ilion; Latin: Troia, Ilium,[1] Turkish: Truva) is a legendary city and center of the Trojan War, as described in the Epic Cycle, and especially in the Iliad, one of the two epic poems attributed to Homer. Trojan refers to the inhabitants and culture of Troy.
